data.title: 7508 Icke
data.text:
Icke

Asteroid number 7508, Icke, was discovered October 16, 1977 by CJ van Houten, Ingrid van Houten-Groeneveld, and Tom Gehrels at Palomar Mountain Observatory. It has a period of 4 years, 250 days.

It was named for Dutch astronomer Vincent Icke (born 1946), an astronomy popularizer and specialist in theoretical investigations of celestial bodies.

Vincent Icke

Its influence seems to be what its name suggests, though: "icky."
